**spawn** — Stream-based, efficient for large output:
```ts
import { spawn } from 'child_process';

const ls = spawn('ls', ['-la', '/usr']);

ls.stdout.on('data', (data) => {
  console.log(`stdout: ${data}`);
});

ls.stderr.on('data', (data) => {
  console.error(`stderr: ${data}`);
});

ls.on('close', (code) => {
  console.log(`Process exited with code ${code}`);
});
```

**fork** — Node.js processes with IPC:
```ts
// parent.ts
import { fork } from 'child_process';

const child = fork('./worker.js');

child.send({ type: 'PROCESS', data: largeArray });

child.on('message', (result) => {
  console.log('Result:', result);
});

// worker.js
process.on('message', async (msg) => {
  if (msg.type === 'PROCESS') {
    const result = heavyComputation(msg.data);
    process.send(result);
  }
});
```

**So sánh**:
| Method | Use Case | Output | IPC |
|--------|----------|--------|-----|
| exec | Simple commands | Buffered | No |
| spawn | Long-running, streaming | Stream | No |
| fork | Node.js workers | Stream | Yes |

**CPU-bound Work Pattern**:
```ts
